{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":22829,"record_hash":"sha256:02366bd2505d44fafe35d574fe626388a2b9a9cf9317aae4175d366310ae9879","timestamp":"2026-05-10T22:42:26.177Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"{\"previous_status\":{\"completed\":\"**Findings**\\n- [P2] Optional association after an already-captured transcript is untested. `record_transcript` intentionally returns a `session_key` when the transcript has records, even if `records_written == 0`, and `run_from_dir` uses that for `--associate-target` ([capture.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/capture.rs:17), [cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:54)). Current tests only associate on first capture or call `associate_session` directly, so a regression tying association to “new records written” would pass ([cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:132), [gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:430)).\\n\\n- [P2] The durable session/source identity contract is under-protected. Docs require `session-key` from provider session id and `source-key` from canonical transcript path, allowing multiple sources under one durable session ([first-poc-implementation.md]([REDACTED:entropy].md:199)). The code implements that split ([capture.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/capture.rs:19)), but tests only exercise one source and even use `only_source_key`, so path-based session keys or conflated source/session keys could slip through ([gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:247), [gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:314)).\\n\\n- [P2] The “association only stores a relationship reference” doc contract is not asserted. Docs say non-project targets should not receive transcript copies, only `gitbutler:agent-sessions` ([first-poc-implementation.md]([REDACTED:entropy].md:281), [requirements-and-goals.md]([REDACTED:entropy].md:70)). The implementation currently matches that ([gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:96)), but tests only check the set entry, not absence of session/transcript keys on the associated target ([cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:151), [gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:442)).\\n\\n- [P3] Path-redaction/output privacy is still mostly doc-only. The docs require human output, JSON output, and validation errors not to include full transcript paths ([first-poc-implementation.md]([REDACTED:entropy].md:98), [first-poc-implementation.md]([REDACTED:entropy].md:315)). Tests cover success prose and parse errors, but not `but --json agentlog capture` or missing/unreadable transcript runtime errors ([cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:101), [but/src/lib.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/lib.rs:1484), [capture.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/capture.rs:13)).\\n\\n`cargo test -p but-agentlog` passes: 18 tests.\"}}","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-10T22:42:26.177Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}